description.en: This ontology puts together all the ontology modules and ODPs that form the RBEEPSA Ontology.

comment.en: A quality of a feature of interest that can be observed.
The ratio of the distance covered by moving air to the time quantity taken to cover it.
The description of how a thing is placed in the space it is in.
A sensor that observes the environment
A sensor that observes the atmospheric pressure
An system that heats, cools and ventilates a given space
A sensor that observes the light
An execution made by an actuator implementing an actuating procedure.
An agent that implements a procedure to sense a change in a real worlds quality and produces an Observation.
A device that enables the remote control and monitoring of the device plugged in
An observation estimated by a predictive model implementing a predictive procedure.
The pressure exerted by the atmosphere as a consequence of gravitational attraction exerted upon the column of air lying directly above the point in question.
A sensor that observes the ammonia levels
It is the power per unit area received from the Sun in the form of electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of the measuring instrument. (Source Wikipedia).
The usage or intended usage ratio of a given space.
A sensor that observes the humidity
A procedure specifying how to impute an event.
A sensor that observes the cloud cover

comment.undefined: An agent that produces an event (Execution) by implementing a procedure.

comment.en: The cooling effect of wind blowing on a surface.
Resource consumption and generation is about the consumption of non-renewable, or the consumption or generation of renewable resources (Source: Wikipedia)
The amount of gas consumed.
The amount of water consumed.
A sensor that observes the CO2 levels
Carbon Dioxide (CO2) measure in the atmosphere. (Defined by m3-lite)
An observation that stands out amongst other observations and does not conform to the expected behaviour
A quantity representing the amount of water vapour indoors.
A quality related to the atmosphere and its phenomena.
An actuator that controls the opening and/or closing of a door
An actuator that controls the opening and/or closing of a window

comment.undefined: An event made by an agent executing a task implemented by a procedure.

comment.en: A sensor that observes the temperature
Measure of cloud cover at a certain time.
A sensor that senses the direction of the Sun to measure the position of the sun or other light sources with respect to the sensor position.
A procedure specifying how to predict an event.
The degree or intensity of heat present outdoors.

comment.undefined: A quality of a feature of interest. An aspect of a feature of interest that is intrinsec to and cannot exist without the feature of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.

comment.en: An agent that implements a procedure to predict an unknown or future event
A sensor that detects the movement

A quality related to the thermal comfort. According to the ANSI/ASHRAE Standard 55-2017, thermal comfort is defined as follows: "that condition of mind that expresses satisfaction with the thermal environment and is assessed by subjective evaluation"
The position of the Sun in the sky is a function of both time and the geographic coordinates of the observer on the surface of the Earth. (Source Wikipedia).

An electricity meter, electric meter, electrical meter, or energy meter is a meter that measures the amount of electric energy consumed by a residence, a business, or an electrically powered device (defined by SEAS Smart Meter ontology).
A sensor that observes the precipitation type, intensity, or quantity
The degree or intensity of heat present indoors.
A water meter is a Meter designed to measure the quantity of water that flows through a pipe. The water meter can measures water consumption or water supply (defined by SEAS Smart Meter ontology)

comment.undefined: A feature of interest is an abstraction of a real world phenomena (object, event, etc). A feature of interest is then described in terms of its properties or qualities, which are qualifiable, quantifiable, observable or operable qualities of the feature of interest.

comment.en: A procedure specifying how to act on an event.
A procedure specifying how to sense an event.

A gas meter is a meter, used to measure the volume of fuel gases such as natural gas and propane. Gas meters are used at residential, commercial, and industrial buildings that consume fuel gas supplied by a gas utility (defined by SEAS Smart Meter ontology).
A sensor that observes the solar radiation
A meter that measures the amount of heat consumed
The amount of electricity generated.
It is the altitude of the sun, the angle between the horizon and the centre of the sun's disc.
It is any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour that falls under gravity.
A collection of executions
An agent that implements a procedure to compute an estimation of missing values
An empty or null event for attributes where a value should have been recorded
An actuator that controls the activation, deactivation or regulation of a lamp or similar device that produces light
The geodetic azimuth of the direction from which the wind is blowing.
An execution made by an executor to estimate or calculate a quality of a feature of interest
An agent that implements a procedure to act on a real worlds quality.
A quality of a feature of interest that can be acted on.
A sensor that observes the wind speed
The amount of electricity consumed.
An observation estimated by an imputation method implementing an imputation procedure.
A quantity representing the amount of water vapour outdoors.
A system that observes the consumption/generation of an entity.
An actuator that controls the regulation of a device or system that heats or cools.
Measure of the concentration of Ammonia (NH3) gas suspended in the atmosphere. (Defined by m3-lite)
A meter that measures the amount of electricity generated
Illuminance is the total luminous flux incident on a surface, per unit area. (Defined by m3-lite)
An actuator that controls the opening and/or closing of a blind

comment.undefined: A workflow, protocol, plan, algorithm, or computational method specifying how to produce an event.

comment.en: A sensor that observes the air quality
The amount of heat consumed.

comment.undefined: Relation that links an agent (Executor) to a procedure that it implements.

comment.en: The location where an event takes place.
Relation that links an execution to the collection of executions it belongs to.
The time instant or interval when an event happens of has its effect. This temporal entity can be past, current or future.

comment.undefined: A relation between features of interest and qualities.
A relation between qualities. A quality is affected by another quality if the value of the latter affects the value of the former.
A relation that links an execution to the procedure used in making the execution through an executor agent.
A relation between qualities and features of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.

comment.en: The link between an execution and the RDF Literal representing the value associated to it.
Relation that links a collection of executions to an execution belonging to that collection.

comment.undefined: Relation that links an executor to the qualities acted upon by the executions it made.
Relation that links an execution to the quality it is acting upon.
Relation that links an execution to the quality it is acting upon.
A relation that links an execution to the procedure used in making the execution through an executor agent.
A relation between qualities and features of interest. Every quality belongs to the feature of interest it is intrinsic to.
Relation that links an execution to the executor that made the execution.
Relation that links an execution to the feature of interest it is acting upon.
Relation that links an executor to the features of interest of the executions it made.

comment.en: The link between an execution and the RDF URI representing the value associated to it.
The time instant when an execution is generated.

comment.undefined: Relation that links an execution to the executor that made the execution.
